<div><h3>CMLT 125 - Imagining Latin Americas </h3>  <hr>What does it mean to be &#8220;Latin American&#8221;? Students in this course will grapple with this question as they analyze the work of Jorge Luis Borges (Argentina), Pablo Neruda (Chile) and Gabriel Garcia Marquez (Colombia), foundational writers who managed to gain a wide readership not only in their countries of origin, but also throughout Europe and the United States. Taught in English. Knowledge of Spanish helpful, but not required; all readings available in translation.  <br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> GP, DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> bi-annually<br><br></div>		</td>
